.TH "of_phy_connect" 9 "of_phy_connect" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
of_phy_connect \- Connect to the phy described in the device tree
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct phy_device *" of_phy_connect
.BI "(struct net_device *dev "  ","
.BI "struct device_node *phy_np "  ","
.BI "void (*hndlr)(struct net_device *) "  ","
.BI "u32 flags "  ","
.BI "phy_interface_t iface "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
pointer to net_device claiming the phy
.IP "phy_np" 12
Pointer to device tree node for the PHY
.IP "hndlr" 12
Link state callback for the network device
.IP "flags" 12
flags to pass to the PHY
.IP "iface" 12
PHY data interface type
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
If successful, returns a pointer to the phy_device with the embedded
struct device refcount incremented by one, or NULL on failure. The
refcount must be dropped by calling \fBphy_disconnect\fP or \fBphy_detach\fP.
